 hari ravichandran “we expect that this expanded role will ensure consistency within the organization as the company evolves and we transition leadership”endurance also announced the appointment of allen m chaves jr as the company’s new chief technology officer chaves brings  years of technology strategy and software architecture experience with him to endurance where he will spearhead the vision and strategic direction for all of the company’s software offerings he will directly lead the software engineering teams for endurance and will work closely with executive management to implement platforms that support the business strategy ensuring endurance’s products technology platforms and architectures evolve to support emerging customer and market opportunities“we’re pleased to have allen join our team to help improve the technology capabilities of our software offerings across our key brands” said hari ravichandran “as we continue to make operational improvements across the company we’re committed to investing in the right talent to help us become better positioned in the marketplace i’m confident that with allen’s leadership and platform architecture expertise we’re well on our way to meeting our business goals”chaves has led the technology architecture teams at several notable technology organizations he joins endurance after serving most recently as chief software architect for ultimate software where he led the technology strategy and architecture for ultimate’s saas products shared services big data and cloudpreviously chaves served as chief architect and director of engineering for the quickbooks online platform at intuit in this role chaves was responsible for all aspects of the technology and architecture of an m business unit and led a team of senior engineering leaders and architects he also held the position of principal software architect for sage where he led the creation of sage’s saas hrms productchaves holds a bachelor of science degree in computer science from the universidade federal de minas gerais in brazil forwardlooking statements this press release includes certain “forwardlooking statements” within the meaning of the private securities litigation reform act of  section a of the securities act of  as amended and section e of the securities exchange act of  as amended including statements concerning our beliefs and expectations about our future executive leadership organizational structure and contributions of mr montagner and mr chaves these forwardlooking statements include but are not limited to plans objectives expectations and intentions and other statements contained in this press release that are not historical facts and statements identified by words such as “expects” “believes” “estimates” “will” “may” “continue” “confident” and variations of such words or words of similar meaning and the use of future dates these forwardlooking statements reflect our current views about our plans intentions expectations strategies and prospects which are based on the information currently available to us and on assumptions we have made although we believe that our plans intentions expectations strategies and prospects as reflected in or suggested by those forwardlooking statements are reasonable we can give no assurance that these plans intentions expectations or strategies will be attained or achieved furthermore actual results may differ materially from those described in the forwardlooking statements and will be affected by a variety of risks and factors that are beyond our control including without limitation the risks set forth under the caption “risk factors” in our quarterly report on form q for the period ended march   filed with the sec on may   and other reports we file with the sec we assume no obligation to update any forwardlooking statements contained in this document as a result of new information future events or otherwiseread moreabout endurance international group endurance international group 